Israel wants Hamas to lay down its weapons and return the bodies of two Israeli soldiers killed in the war.
A new phase of indirect negotiations is expected to begin later this month in Egypt.
More than 2,100 Palestinians were killed in the war, three-quarters of whom were civilians, and at least 494 children, according to estimates by the Palestinian side and the UN.
