MEPs have proposed to accelerate the entry into force of the Personal Data Act
In case of success of the initiative, the data of the Russians will not be stored on servers abroad from 1 January 2015.
The State Duma has submitted a draft law, which provides for the transfer of the date of entry into force of the already adopted law on personal data of Russians - from 1 September 2016 to 1 January 2015.
The initiative is placed on the basis of the legislative activities of the lower chamber.
Its authors were the deputies of the State Duma Vadim Dengin, Yaroslav Nilov (LDPR), Evgeny Fedorov (“United Russia”), Vladimir Parahin (“Just Russia”) and Alexander Yushchenko (KPRF).
Such a change, according to the authors of the initiative, will contribute to a more efficient and efficient guarantee of the rights of citizens of the Russian Federation to the security of personal data and the secrecy of correspondence in information and telecommunications networks.
The law, whose entry into force is urgent for parliamentarians, obliges to store in the territory of the Russian Federation the personal data of Russians processed over the Internet.
It also makes mandatory the recording, systematization, storage, storage, clarification and extraction of personal data of Russian citizens, in databases located in the territory of Russia, as well as the indication of the location of such databases.
In addition, the law gives Roskomnadzor the right, on the basis of a court decision, to restrict access to information processed in violation of the legislation of the Russian Federation in the field of personal data.
The law also proposes the creation of the so-called "black lists" of infringing websites - the automated information system "Register of infringers of the rights of subjects of personal data".
This law was passed by the State Duma in the summer.
The authors of the bill were Andrey Lugova and Vadim Dengin from LDPR and Alexander Yushchenko from KPRF.
Dengin and Yushchenko are also one of the authors of the current draft law on the date of the entry into force of the already adopted law.
