Putin Granted Russian Citizenship to Ukrainian Five-Boarder
Russian President Vladimir Putin granted Russian citizenship to the famous Ukrainian athlete Anne Buryak.
The relevant decree is published on the Internet portal of legal information.
Earlier this year, the athlete moved to Russia to a permanent residence and turned to the Federation of modern five-man with a request to give her the opportunity to play for the Russian team.
In 2013, she won two World Cup stages, won the silver medal of the European Championship in the personal championship and became the world champion in a mixed batch, which is one of the new types of program in this sport.
